<header class="article-header"><h1 itemprop="headline">What Is Pump.fun? Complete Guide to Solana's Meme Coin Launchpad 2026</h1><div class="article-meta"><time datetime="2026-06-03" itemprop="datePublished">June 3, 2026</time><span class="read-time">6 min read</span></div></header>
<div class="article-content" itemprop="articleBody">
<p class="lead">Pump.fun has become the dominant meme coin launchpad on Solana in 2026. Thousands of tokens launch daily, and a small fraction "graduate" to Raydium where they can reach mainstream audiences. Understanding Pump.fun is essential for any serious meme coin trader.</p>
<section><h2>How Pump.fun Works</h2><p>Pump.fun is a fair-launch platform that lets anyone create a Solana meme coin with zero coding. The process:<ol><li><strong>Create:</strong> Choose a name, ticker, and upload an image. Pay a small creation fee.</li><li><strong>Bonding curve:</strong> The token launches on a bonding curve ” the earlier you buy, the cheaper it is. Price increases as more tokens are purchased.</li><li><strong>Graduation:</strong> When the token reaches $100K market cap on the bonding curve, liquidity is automatically deposited to Raydium, a major Solana DEX.</li><li><strong>Post-graduation:</strong> The token now trades on Raydium with standard decentralized exchange mechanics.</li></ol></p></section>
<section><h2>Trading Strategy for Pump.fun Tokens</h2><ul><li><strong>Pre-graduation entry:</strong> Buy at $20K-$50K market cap. High risk, highest reward. Most tokens never graduate.</li><li><strong>Graduation entry:</strong> Buy when liquidity hits Raydium. This is the moment of maximum volatility ” the price often dumps as early holders take profits, then recovers.</li><li><strong>Post-graduation hold:</strong> If the community is strong and volume continues, the token can 5-10x from graduation price over 24-72 hours.</li></ul>
<p>Green flags for Pump.fun tokens: Verified Twitter, Telegrams with 200+ real members, unique branding, and a team that's active in the community.</p></section>
<section><h2>Risks on Pump.fun</h2><ul><li>~99% of Pump.fun tokens never graduate. They die on the bonding curve.</li><li>Bots dominate early entries ” humans rarely get the cheapest prices.</li><li>Copycat tokens and scams exist on the platform.</li><li>Post-graduation dumps can be brutal ” early buyers take 5-10x profits immediately.</li></ul>
<p><strong>Never invest more than 1-2% of your portfolio on Pump.fun launches.</strong> Most will go to zero. But the ones that graduate can pay for all your losses and more.</p></section>
